1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,889
A lot of people, maybe even a majority, may laugh at this success-rewarding technique.

2
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:10,930
That's because they refuse to believe that success comes from managed thinking.

3
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:14,930
But please, don't accept the judgment of average people.

4
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:16,609
You are not average.

5
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:23,010
If you have any doubts as to the basic soundness of the sell-yourself-to-yourself principle,

6
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:26,930
ask the most successful person you know what he thinks about it.

7
00:00:27,199 --> 00:00:31,330
Ask him, and then start selling yourself to yourself.

8
00:00:33,359 --> 00:00:35,249
Upgrade your thinking.

9
00:00:35,280 --> 00:00:37,810
Think like important people think.

10
00:00:38,879 --> 00:00:43,890
Upgrading your thinking upgrades your actions, and this produces success.

11
00:00:44,399 --> 00:00:50,450
Here is an easy way to help you make more of yourself by thinking like important people think.

12
00:00:50,639 --> 00:00:53,410
Use the following form as a guide.

13
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:56,769
How am I thinking checklist.

14
00:00:57,359 --> 00:00:59,810
Situation, when I worry.

15
00:01:00,079 --> 00:01:04,290
Ask yourself, would an important person worry about this?

16
00:01:04,399 --> 00:01:08,769
Would the most successful person I know be disturbed about this?

17
00:01:10,159 --> 00:01:12,209
Situation, an idea.

18
00:01:12,719 --> 00:01:17,890
Ask yourself, what would an important person do if he had this idea?

19
00:01:19,199 --> 00:01:21,490
Situation, my appearance.

20
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:26,609
Ask yourself, do I look like someone who has maximum self-respect?

21
00:01:27,919 --> 00:01:30,129
Situation, my language.

22
00:01:30,479 --> 00:01:35,649
Ask yourself, am I using the language of successful people?

23
00:01:36,159 --> 00:01:38,209
Situation, what I read.

24
00:01:38,479 --> 00:01:42,129
Ask yourself, would an important person read this?

25
00:01:43,519 --> 00:01:45,570
Situation, conversation.

26
00:01:46,079 --> 00:01:50,530
Ask yourself, is this something successful people would discuss?

27
00:01:51,919 --> 00:01:52,769
Situation.

28
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:54,450
When I lose my temper.

29
00:01:54,639 --> 00:01:59,570
Ask yourself, Would an important person get mad at what I'm mad at?

30
00:02:00,559 --> 00:02:01,490
Situation.

31
00:02:01,519 --> 00:02:02,609
My jokes.

32
00:02:02,879 --> 00:02:07,490
Ask yourself, Is this the kind of joke an important person would tell?

33
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,729
Situation.

34
00:02:09,839 --> 00:02:10,769
My job.

35
00:02:11,119 --> 00:02:16,769
Ask yourself, How does an important person describe his job to others?

36
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:23,729
Cement in your mind the question, Is this the way an important person does it?

37
00:02:24,079 --> 00:02:28,530
Use this question to make you a bigger, more successful person.

38
00:02:29,119 --> 00:02:32,450
In a nutshell, remember 1.

39
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:33,810
Look important.

40
00:02:33,839 --> 00:02:35,810
It helps you think important.

41
00:02:35,999 --> 00:02:37,890
Your appearance talks to you.

42
00:02:38,079 --> 00:02:41,729
Be sure it lifts your spirits and builds your confidence.

43
00:02:41,919 --> 00:02:43,970
Your appearance talks to others.

44
00:02:44,079 --> 00:02:50,689
Make certain, it says, here is an important person, intelligent, prosperous, and dependable.

45
00:02:50,689 --> 00:02:52,450
2.

46
00:02:52,879 --> 00:02:54,930
Think your work is important.

47
00:02:55,119 --> 00:03:00,370
Think this way, and you will receive mental signals on how to do your job better.

48
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:06,530
Think your work is important, and your subordinates will think their work is important, too.

49
00:03:06,559 --> 00:03:08,370
3.

50
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:11,970
Give yourself a pep talk several times daily.

51
00:03:12,159 --> 00:03:15,490
Build a sell-yourself-to-yourself commercial.

52
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:20,450
Remind yourself at every opportunity that you're a first-class person.

53
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:21,729
4.

54
00:03:21,999 --> 00:03:28,450
In all of life's situations, ask yourself, is this the way an important person thinks?

55
00:03:28,639 --> 00:03:30,930
Then obey the answer.